{"word":"νησιώτης","slug":"νησιώτης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νησιώτης</b></el> <el>(νησιώτης, ου, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νῆσος'><el>νῆσος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>an islander</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>of</i> or <i>in an island, insular</i> , <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>νησιῶτις πέτρα</el> an <i>island</i> rock, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}